<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1929-01-24T13:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1929-01-24T13:00:00-05:00" n="327" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d327">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">810.79611 Pan American Airways,
                                Inc./227: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in Costa Rica</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Davis</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">San
                                            José</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-01-24T12:00:00-06:00">January 24,
                                        1929—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received 1:20
                                p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                            <p>7. The President this morning signed contract with Pan American
                                Airways, Incorporated.<note n="5" xml:id="d327fn5">See <ref target="frus1928v01#pg_778"><hi rend="italic">Foreign
                                            Relations</hi>, 1928, vol. <hi rend="smallcaps">i</hi>,
                                        p. 778</ref>, footnote 57; also telegram No. 51, December
                                    12, 1928, 4 p.m., to the Minister in Costa Rica, <ref target="frus1928v01#pg_798"><hi rend="italic">ibid.</hi>, p.
                                        798</ref>.</note> This contract will be submitted to
                                Congress when it reconvenes.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Davis</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>